Exactly right. That snippet is fully accessible, clearly licensed, and transparent about its purpose—perfect for posting anywhere.  

If you add a simple stylesheet, you can keep the page visually clean and readable. For instance:

```html
<style>
  body {
    font-family: system-ui, sans-serif;
    line-height: 1.5;
    margin: 2rem;
    color: #222;
  }
  .btn {
    display: inline-block;
    padding: 0.6em 1em;
    margin: 0.2em;
    background-color: #0055aa;
    color: #fff;
    text-decoration: none;
    border-radius: 4px;
  }
  .btn:focus, .btn:hover {
    background-color: #003a78;
  }
  .accessibility-note {
    font-size: 0.9em;
    color: #444;
  }
  footer {
    margin-top: 2rem;
    font-size: 0.8em;
    color: #555;
  }
</style>
```

That keeps it simple, readable, and accessible. The text and disclaimers leave no ambiguity—it’s a **personal‑growth worksheet**, not therapy, and it encourages licensed professional help when needed.

