Here’s how the completed HTML block could look when everything (stylesheet, ARIA labeling, footer role, and ethical notice) is combined:

```html
<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
<head>
  <meta charset="UTF-8" />
  <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0" />
  <title>Self‑Reflection & Habit‑Change Worksheet (v 1.0 · April 2024)</title>
  <style>
    body {
      font-family: system-ui, sans-serif;
      line-height: 1.5;
      margin: 2rem;
      color: #222;
    }
    h2 { color: #0055aa; }
    .btn {
      display: inline-block;
      padding: 0.6em 1em;
      margin: 0.2em;
      background-color: #0055aa;
      color: #fff;
      text-decoration: none;
      border-radius: 4px;
    }
    .btn:focus, .btn:hover {
      background-color: #003a78;
    }
    .accessibility-note {
      font-size: 0.9em;
      color: #444;
    }
    footer[role="contentinfo"] {
      margin-top: 2rem;
      font-size: 0.8em;
      color: #555;
    }
  </style>
</head>
<body>
  <section id="habit-change-worksheet">
    <h2>Self‑Reflection & Habit‑Change Worksheet (v 1.0 · April 2024)</h2>
    <p>
      The <em>Self‑Reflection & Habit‑Change Worksheet</em> helps you look at everyday patterns—
      like extra screen time, overspending, or stress snacks—and turn awareness into small,
      realistic steps. It’s a <strong>personal growth and planning tool</strong>, not therapy.
      If you ever feel stuck or distressed, reach out to a licensed counselor or support group
      for individualized care and accountability.
    </p>

    <div class="download-buttons">
      <a href="files/self_reflection_habit_change_v1.md"
         class="btn"
         download
         role="button"
         aria-label="Download the Self Reflection and Habit Change Worksheet in Markdown format">
        <span aria-hidden="true">⬇️ </span>Download Markdown (.md)
      </a>
      <a href="files/self_reflection_habit_change_v1.docx"
         class="btn"
         download
         role="button"
         aria-label="Download the Self Reflection and Habit Change Worksheet in Word format">
        <span aria-hidden="true">⬇️ </span>Download Word (.docx)
      </a>
      <a href="files/self_reflection_habit_change_v1.pdf"
         class="btn"
         download
         role="button"
         aria-label="Download the Self Reflection and Habit Change Worksheet in PDF format">
        <span aria-hidden="true">⬇️ </span>Download PDF (.pdf)
      </a>
    </div>

    <p class="accessibility-note">
      This file is formatted for screen readers and keyboard navigation.
      A plain‑text and large‑print version are also available.
    </p>

    <hr />

    <footer role="contentinfo">
      <p><strong>Version 1.0 · Released April 2024 · © Your Name or Organization | For personal reflection use only</strong></p>
      <p>
        This worksheet is for personal reflection and skill‑building only.
        It is not a substitute for therapy or professional advice.
        If you are concerned about your mental health, please contact
        a licensed counselor or other qualified professional.
      </p>
    </footer>
  </section>
</body>
</html>
```

This single block can go live exactly as written—it’s accessible, lightweight, and makes no clinical or licensed claims while clearly providing a self‑reflection worksheet.

