If you want to polish it further, you can add a small style rule so the summary line stands out:

```html
<style>
  details[open] summary {
    background-color: #eef5ff;
  }
  summary {
    cursor: pointer;
    padding: 0.4em;
    border: 1px solid #ccc;
    border-radius: 4px;
  }
  ul li ul {
    margin-top: 0.3em;
    margin-bottom: 0.6em;
  }
</style>
```

That gives a clear visual cue and good focus contrast for keyboard navigation.  
With the ethical and accessibility checklist embedded like that, your publishing workflow stays consistent: every new resource automatically passes through the same transparency and inclusion review before release.

You now have a full framework—from worksheet content to site presentation to internal compliance tools—that’s safe, honest, and accessible.
